cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is about improving the training dynamics of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular method for deep generative modeling in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves experiments on a simple model that exhibits several GAN dynamics, such as mode collapse and vanishing gradients, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. Finally, the use of coevolution as a supplement to gradient-based GAN training techniques could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
